DataElement.preferredName: E-Selectin Median Fluorescence Intensity 6 digits 2 Decimal Number
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The value expressed, as a number with 6 total digits with 2 digits after the decimal, for the unit of measure equal to the geometric mean fluorescence intensity of a log-normal distribution of fluorescence signals related to E-selectin (this protein is involved in leukocyte adhesion, migration and rolling).

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: E-selectin (610 aa, ~67 kDa) is encoded by the human SELE gene. This protein is involved in leukocyte adhesion, migration and rolling._A unit of measure equal to the geometric mean fluorescence intensity of a log-normal distribution of fluorescence signals.
